WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.740
chapter number one, and we've been studying

00:00:02.740 --> 00:00:04.440
on Sunday mornings here in our church

00:00:04.440 --> 00:00:06.880
through the book of 1st and 2nd Timothy.

00:00:06.880 --> 00:00:08.779
You see the banners on the wall behind me.

00:00:08.779 --> 00:00:11.380
Our theme for this year is continue,

00:00:11.380 --> 00:00:13.960
and this morning being Friend Day,

00:00:13.960 --> 00:00:15.260
I was praying about where to go,

00:00:15.260 --> 00:00:17.680
and the Lord led me here to the book of Ephesians.

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:19.760
It's a wonderful book, the book of Ephesians,

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:22.260
and here in this book, we find that God

00:00:22.260 --> 00:00:24.520
helps the people of God, his children,

00:00:24.520 --> 00:00:27.899
to understand their position in Christ.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.739
We find the first three chapters really deal with that,

00:00:30.739 --> 00:00:32.299
and in the last half of the book,

00:00:32.299 --> 00:00:34.479
the last three chapters deal with our walk,

00:00:34.479 --> 00:00:36.299
now that we're saved, here's how we live,

00:00:36.299 --> 00:00:38.939
here's how we behave, and what a blessing

00:00:38.939 --> 00:00:42.139
to know this wonderful book and the truth

00:00:42.139 --> 00:00:43.659
that's contained therein.

00:00:43.659 --> 00:00:46.720
We find that the apostle Paul had a brief stop

00:00:46.720 --> 00:00:48.900
in the city of Ephesus near the end

00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:50.479
of his second missionary journey.

00:00:50.479 --> 00:00:52.819
You could read of that in Acts chapter 18,

00:00:52.819 --> 00:00:55.340
and verses 18 and 19, and we find that

00:00:55.340 --> 00:00:57.639
as he was briefly held in Ephesus,

00:00:58.400 --> 00:00:59.959
that there was a request by those in Ephesus

00:00:59.959 --> 00:01:03.439
that he stay longer, but he had a need to depart,

00:01:03.439 --> 00:01:05.519
and we find that he said to them

00:01:05.519 --> 00:01:09.019
that he would return if the Lord allowed,

00:01:09.019 --> 00:01:11.360
and we find that during the third missionary journey,

00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:14.000
as it's recorded for us in Acts 19,

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:16.519
that the apostle Paul had the opportunity

00:01:16.519 --> 00:01:18.220
to return to the city of Ephesus.

00:01:18.220 --> 00:01:21.099
In fact, he ministered there for about three years,

00:01:21.099 --> 00:01:24.040
and during those three years that he's in Ephesus,

00:01:24.040 --> 00:01:27.199
we're told that all of those within Asia Minor

00:01:27.199 --> 00:01:30.239
heard the word of the Lord, and what a blessing

00:01:30.239 --> 00:01:33.419
to think about the ministry that God gave

00:01:33.419 --> 00:01:36.360
for the apostle Paul there in Ephesus.

00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:38.519
I believe that as you look at the 19th chapter

00:01:38.519 --> 00:01:41.699
of the book of Acts, that there in the city of Ephesus,

00:01:41.699 --> 00:01:43.239
they experienced revival.

00:01:43.239 --> 00:01:44.879
There were many people that were saved,

00:01:44.879 --> 00:01:48.239
and many people that just got serious

00:01:48.239 --> 00:01:51.919
about living for the Lord and serving the Lord,

00:01:51.959 --> 00:01:54.599
and we find that Paul eventually would have to leave

00:01:54.599 --> 00:01:59.599
from Ephesus and various reasons concerning his departure,

00:01:59.879 --> 00:02:03.360
but we find that Timothy was left to minister there

00:02:03.360 --> 00:02:05.080
at the church at Ephesus.

00:02:05.080 --> 00:02:07.699
In fact, as we've studied in 1 and 2 Timothy,

00:02:07.699 --> 00:02:10.479
those that have been with us throughout this calendar year,

00:02:10.479 --> 00:02:12.960
you find that many times we have referenced

00:02:12.960 --> 00:02:16.800
how the apostle Paul is providing instruction to Timothy

00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:20.360
with regard to the ministry there in Ephesus.

00:02:20.360 --> 00:02:22.279
We find that there's a period of time

00:02:22.279 --> 00:02:26.160
that passes between Paul's departure and this letter

00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:28.360
that is called the book of Ephesians

00:02:28.360 --> 00:02:31.080
being written to these individuals.

00:02:31.080 --> 00:02:33.880
We find that in verse number one, he refers to them,

00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:37.039
notice with me, it says, Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ,

00:02:37.039 --> 00:02:41.800
by the will of God, to the saints which are at Ephesus

00:02:41.800 --> 00:02:44.479
